{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778980585440,"sessionID":"ses_1cc86d111ffeY08e3sGmsuZb8d","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_TrDHhszAFxs4G5c5qbdkfOah","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- removed the `EC:1.4.3.22` broadMatch from `histamine oxidase activity` (`GO:0052598`), leaving that broader EC mapping on `diamine oxidase activity` (`GO:0052597`)\n+- reparented `protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity` (`GO:0004720`) from `diamine oxidase activity` to `GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor`\n+\n+The ontology validates after these changes.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This PR addresses issue #31964 by correcting the `diamine oxidase activity` subtree and its EC mapping usage.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- removed `xref: EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\"skos:broadMatch\"}` from `GO:0052598 histamine oxidase activity`\n+- changed the parent of `GO:0004720 protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity` from `GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity` to `GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- `EC:1.4.3.22` is broader than `histamine oxidase activity`, so the broad match belongs on the parent `GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity`, not on the histamine-specific child term\n+- `protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity` acts on a protein substrate and is not a diamine oxidase, but it does belong under the broader CH-NH2 donor oxidoreductase class (`GO:0016641`)\n+\n+Checks performed:\n+- reviewed the issue context and confirmed the requested intent was clear\n+- inspected the relevant GO stanzas in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- confirmed EC labels with `runoak`:\n+  - `EC:1.4.3.22` = diamine oxidase\n+  - `EC:1.4.3.13` = protein-lysine 6-oxidase\n+  - `EC:1.4.3.10` = putrescine oxidase\n+- edited via the standard GO checkout/checkin workflow using `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- ran `make travis_build` in `src/ontology`, which passed\n+\n+Checklist:\n+- [x] PLAN: issue reviewed and requested changes identified\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated in the course of `make travis_build`\n+- [ ] RESEARCH: not needed for this targeted classification/mapping fix\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: relevant GO terms and EC mappings inspected\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: not applicable beyond checking existing catalytic activity structure and mapping practice\n+- [x] EDITS: used checkout/checkin workflow with term files\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parentage corrected without adding over-specific axioms\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: mapping and reaction guidance applied\n+- [x] METADATA: no new terms created; existing metadata preserved\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: no new references introduced\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Summary:\n+- removed the `EC:1.4.3.22` broadMatch from `histamine oxidase activity` (`GO:0052598`), leaving that broader EC mapping on `diamine oxidase activity` (`GO:0052597`)\n+- reparented `protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity` (`GO:0004720`) from `diamine oxidase activity` to `GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor`\n+\n+The ontology validates after these changes.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+This PR addresses issue #31964 by correcting the `diamine oxidase activity` subtree and its EC mapping usage.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+- removed `xref: EC:1.4.3.22 {source=\"skos:broadMatch\"}` from `GO:0052598 histamine oxidase activity`\n+- changed the parent of `GO:0004720 protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity` from `GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity` to `GO:0016641 oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- `EC:1.4.3.22` is broader than `histamine oxidase activity`, so the broad match belongs on the parent `GO:0052597 diamine oxidase activity`, not on the histamine-specific child term\n+- `protein-lysine 6-oxidase activity` acts on a protein substrate and is not a diamine oxidase, but it does belong under the broader CH-NH2 donor oxidoreductase class (`GO:0016641`)\n+\n+Checks performed:\n+- reviewed the issue context and confirmed the requested intent was clear\n+- inspected the relevant GO stanzas in `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`\n+- confirmed EC labels with `runoak`:\n+  - `EC:1.4.3.22` = diamine oxidase\n+  - `EC:1.4.3.13` = protein-lysine 6-oxidase\n+  - `EC:1.4.3.10` = putrescine oxidase\n+- edited via the standard GO checkout/checkin workflow using `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl`\n+- ran `make travis_build` in `src/ontology`, which passed\n+\n+Checklist:\n+- [x] PLAN: issue reviewed and requested changes identified\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: ontology validated in the course of `make travis_build`\n+- [ ] RESEARCH: not needed for this targeted classification/mapping fix\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: relevant GO terms and EC mappings inspected\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: not applicable beyond checking existing catalytic activity structure and mapping practice\n+- [x] EDITS: used checkout/checkin workflow with term files\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parentage corrected without adding over-specific axioms\n+- [x] SPECIA